SIMPLE: impotent
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impotent
<hw>Im"po*tent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>impotent</ets>, L. <ets>impotens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>; pref.
<ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>potens</ets> potent, powerful. See
<er>Potent</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not potent; wanting power,
strength. or vigor. whether physical, intellectual, or moral; deficient
in capacity; destitute of force; weak; feeble; infirm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There sat a certain man at Lystra, <qex>impotent</qex> inhis
feet.</q> <rj><qau>Acts xiv. 8.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O most lame and <qex>impotent</qex> conclusion!</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not slow to hear,⟦br⟧
Nor <qex>impotent</qex> to save.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Wanting the power of self-restraint; incontrolled;
ungovernable; violent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Impotent</qex> of tongue, her silence broke.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Wanting the power of procreation;
unable to copulate; also, sometimes, sterile; barren;</def>
<specif>specifically, in males:</specif> <def>unable to achieve or
sustain a penile erection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impotent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Impotent
<hw>Im"po*tent</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who is impotent.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impotently</ent>⟦br⟧
